# Cloudflare Pages headers.
#
# Force the browser/edge to revalidate the local app bundle on every load so a
# freshly-served HTML page (served DYNAMIC, always current) never pairs with a
# stale cached app.js/config.js. That version skew is what produced the F79
# "Preorders.upsertReservation is not a function" error in prod after a deploy:
# new admin.html + 4-hour-cached old app.js.
#
# Both files send ETags, so `no-cache` (revalidate-before-use) is cheap — a 304
# when unchanged, an immediate fresh copy the moment a deploy changes them.
# config.js is per-branch (prod vs staging keys); revalidating it avoids serving
# a stale key set after a config change for the same reason.
#
# vendor/supabase.min.js is the self-hosted Supabase UMD bundle (pinned
# 2.110.1, replaces the floating jsdelivr @2 tag — 2026-07 review, A11). Same
# no-cache posture so an upgraded bundle can never skew against fresh HTML.
/app.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache
/config.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache
/vendor/supabase.min.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache

# Security headers (2026-07 review, A11).
#
# CSP notes — scoped to what the pages actually use:
# - script-src 'unsafe-inline' is required by the per-page inline <script>
#   blocks and inline onerror handlers (no-build architecture). The value of
#   this policy is blocking *external* script origins — with the Supabase
#   bundle self-hosted, no third-party script host is allowed at all, with
#   one deliberate exception: https://challenges.cloudflare.com (Turnstile's
#   api.js, native-customer-signup S3). frame-src carries the same origin —
#   the widget itself renders in an iframe from there; with no frame-src
#   directive it would fall back to default-src 'self' and the iframe would
#   be blocked exactly like the script was (caught live on staging 2026-07-23:
#   Rick's real-browser signup test hit "script-src" blocked before this fix).
#   connect-src also carries it as a precaution against Turnstile's own
#   background requests, even with pre-clearance off (Cloudflare's own CSP
#   guidance flags connect-src as pre-clearance-relevant; harmless either way).
# - style-src/font-src allow the Google Fonts import in style.css.
# - connect-src lists BOTH Supabase projects so this file merges cleanly
#   between the staging and main branches (config.js picks the live one).
# - img-src https: covers distributor cover CDNs (PRH, Lunar, misc);
#   data: covers the inline SVG cover placeholder.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://challenges.cloudflare.com; frame-src https://challenges.cloudflare.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' https: data:; connect-src 'self' https://plgegklqtdjxeglvyjte.supabase.co https://puoaiyezsreowpwxzxhj.supabase.co https://challenges.cloudflare.com; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
